        &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #3F3F3F;&quot;&gt;The Torah&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #3F3F3F;&quot;&gt;The Torah, the first five books of the Old Testament, is the oldest and most sacred text of the Jews.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #3F3F3F;&quot;&gt;It is believed traditionally to have been given by God to Moses on Mount Sinai. Modern scholarship maintains that it was written by various authors throughout several centuries, probably from the ninth century BCE onward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/body&gt;
        &lt;/html&gt;

