        &lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;The last census before the German occupation, held in January 1941, reported 2,150 Jewish residents in Tyachiv. They were 20% of the total population of the town.&amp;#160; Many of the Jews were merchants; others were craftsmen and agricultural workers and farmers.&amp;#160; The Jewish community was, as were most communities in Eastern Europe, a religious observant Orthodox community.&lt;/p&gt;
