        &lt;p class=&quot;defaultstyle&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: &apos;Gentium Plus&apos;;&quot;&gt;After the war Elimelech Basch&apos;s brother Jacob, who survived the Holocaust, came back and found the diary. He later gave it to Basch&apos;s only remaining daughter - Perhiya - &amp;#160;who lives in Israel. She, in turn, decided to donate the diary for safekeeping to the National library of Israel for the generations to come.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
