        &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;National Libraries all over the world preserve the spiritual and cultural treasures of their peoples.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;Two special features make the treasures of the NLI unique: the first is the antiquity of Jewish tradition: the Jewish people place the start of the nation back in the days of Abraham (c. 1800 BCE), and start recording their history&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;already in 1000BCE; the second &amp;#160;is the fact that since 70 CE, when the Second Temple was destroyed and the Jews were ousted from Jerusalem by the Romans), the Jewish people did not have an independent center and Jewish&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;communities were scattered throughout the Asia and Europe carrying with them their old records and creating new ones.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;The memory of the Jewish people is thus embedded in writings which were created throughout the Jewish world over many generations; these writings bear the spiritual heritage of the Jewish people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;The return of Jews to their ancient homeland presented a great challenge:for the first time after almost 2000 years in the diaspora, treasures from Yemen to Eastern Europe, from South America to Afghanistan (6), could be brought&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;home and assembled under one roof &#8211; the National Library of Israel &amp;#160;&#8211; a place in which the memory of Jewish heritage and of the Holy Land is deposited and curated. Alongside these, many other intellectual treasures of universal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;significance (8) which were kept and acquired throughout the generations were deposited in the library on various occasions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #1F497D;&quot;&gt;This exhibition will follow the trails of several of our most treasured items; each reflecting &amp;#160;the memory of a certain period and place in history.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
